    },
    {
      "id": "i7MFaUGmMI6CPw3oMZz9z",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 8679.862730314266,
      "y": 296.927649071344,
      "width": 1348.6790771484375,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1V",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 25911558,
      "version": 1259,
      "versionNonce": 560717914,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776083327094,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- given that areas where pac man or ghost can move in within the maze can only be 1XN or NX1, \n  then pac man or a ghost can at maximum span 2 maze cells.    \n- collision detection for the given sprites can be considered as a rectangle to rectangle collision detection.\n- would we do collision detection in canvas basis or in maze basis ?\n    - canvas basis, means that we will use the Canvas Rectangle containing the sprite.\n    - maze basis, means that we will use  the maze cell to which the sprite belongs at the current moment, however this is a bit confusing,\n      because moving objects can partially span multiple maze cells.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- given that areas where pac man or ghost can move in within the maze can only be 1XN or NX1, \n  then pac man or a ghost can at maximum span 2 maze cells.    \n- collision detection for the given sprites can be considered as a rectangle to rectangle collision detection.\n- would we do collision detection in canvas basis or in maze basis ?\n    - canvas basis, means that we will use the Canvas Rectangle containing the sprite.\n    - maze basis, means that we will use  the maze cell to which the sprite belongs at the current moment, however this is a bit confusing,\n      because moving objects can partially span multiple maze cells.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Kf3359pSuE3rrG4QRZ-LQ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 8672.009941611093,
      "y": 586.7610160569666,
      "width": 737.3394775390625,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1W",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1264912390,
      "version": 387,
      "versionNonce": 446547546,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "id": "HWI_G5fgk6fxvQkxUdg9z",
          "type": "arrow"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1776083800214,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Pac man to Suger and super suger collision detection\n1- get the canvas rectangle of pac man.\n2- get the canvas rectangle of the sugar or the super sugar.\n3- check if the suger rectangle completely lies within the pac man rectangle.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Pac man to Suger and super suger collision detection\n1- get the canvas rectangle of pac man.\n2- get the canvas rectangle of the sugar or the super sugar.\n3- check if the suger rectangle completely lies within the pac man rectangle.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "HWJOozDjoTfUQhz95m9ur",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 8672.00994241706,
      "y": 747.276237158494,
      "width": 614.1195678710938,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1X",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 558597722,
      "version": 319,
      "versionNonce": 848573510,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776083515694,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Pac man to wall collision detection\n1- get the canvas rectangle of pac man.\n2- get the canvas rectangle of the wall\n3- check if there is any intersection between the 2 rectangles.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Pac man to wall collision detection\n1- get the canvas rectangle of pac man.\n2- get the canvas rectangle of the wall\n3- check if there is any intersection between the 2 rectangles.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
